author: app.com
title: Rutgers students come through in "blackout"
text:
MORE PISCATAWAY -- Rutgers called for a blackout during Saturday night’s football game against fourth-ranked Michigan State.
The students delivered.
The 10,000-seat student section was mostly filled -- and completely clad in black -- prior to kickoff.
Some of the non-student fans didn’t get the memo as there was a fair amount of red visible throughout High Point Solutions Stadium.
Hardly any Michigan State green could be seen. This powerhouse does not travel well, apparently.
That will change when Ohio State comes to town in two weeks.
Staff writer Jerry Carino: jcarino@gannettnj.com .
